So today sucks. Morning starts off good... Get to work, still okay... Get a lesson in my college course done, GREAT!

Then the wife calls. Her car stalled out. On the side of a major road that doesn't have a shoulder. Well great, I leave work, get to her and think it's the battery, so we try to jump it (still on the side of the road) and no dice. So luckily we have Roadside Assistance, call them, get it towed after baking in the sun for over an hour.

The kicker? Car died like a mile off post, where she works. She was 1.5 miles away from the auto shop we got it towed to. We just couldn't get it to move far enough to not need the tow -.-

I hope everyone else is having a good day :stuck_out_tongue:
